Here is an improved CSS styling for the students table and overdue charges table to make them look more attractive, structured, and responsive.


---

ðŸ”¹ 1. Update table.component.css (Shared Table Styles)

Since we are using a shared table component, the styling will automatically apply to both Students and Overdue Charges.

/* Table Container */
.table-container {
  background-color: white;
  border-radius: 10px;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  padding: 20px;
  overflow-x: auto;
}

/* Table Styling */
table {
  width: 100%;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  background: white;
}

/* Table Headers */
th {
  background-color: #6A5ACD; /* Nice Purple Shade */
  color: white;
  padding: 12px;
  text-align: left;
  font-size: 16px;
}

/* Table Rows */
td {
  padding: 12px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
  font-size: 14px;
  color: #333;
}

/* Hover Effect */
tr:hover {
  background-color: #f1f1f1;
}

/* Student Image */
.student-img {
  width: 40px;
  height: 40px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  margin-right: 10px;
  vertical-align: middle;
}

/* Responsive Design */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  th, td {
    font-size: 12px;
    padding: 10px;
  }
  .table-container {
    padding: 10px;
  }
}


